                <h1>Cyber Security: A Comprehensive History Timeline</h1>
                <p>Cyber security has evolved significantly since the early days of computing. In the 1970s, the first viruses emerged, leading to the establishment of protocols for data protection. The 1980s saw the rise of firewalls, while the 1990s introduced the concept of ethical hacking. Today, with advanced threats, organizations prioritize cybersecurity strategies to safeguard their systems.</p>
